==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: -zin
<hw>-zin</hw> }</mhw>. <ety>[<ets>Piper</ets>idine + <ets>az</ets>ote +
<ets>-ine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A crystalline substance,
<chform>(C2H4NH)2</chform>, formed by action of ammonia on ethylene
bromide, by reduction of pyrazine, etc. It is a strong base, and is used
as a remedy for gout.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piperic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: -zin
<hw>-zin</hw> }</mhw>. <ety>[<ets>Pyr</ets>idine + Gr. <?/ not + <?/
life.]</ety> <fld>(Org. Chem.)</fld> <def>A feebly basic solid,
<chform>C4H4N2</chform>, obtained by distilling piperazine with zinc
dust, and in other ways. Also, by extension, any of various derivatives
of the same.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pyre</ent>⟦br⟧
